MUSICAL The War of The Worlds is set to return to Glasgow for the final time as part of the show's last ever arena tour. Last War of the Worlds MUSICAL The War of The Worlds is set to return to Glasgow for the final time as part of the show's last ever arena tour.Musician Jeff Wayne will be bringing his The War of The Worlds Alive on Stage show to the Hydro on November 29.Scottish actor Callum O'Neill, who featured in the blockbuster movie Brave, is set to play the author HG Wells, whose books is what the stage show is based on.Tickets cost &pound;38.50. 